task-rest_bold.json.Instructions: Participants were asked to lie still in the scanner, with their eyes closed.
task-rest_bold.json.TaskDescription: No stimuli were shown on the screen. Subjects may have fallen asleep during the scans. A foam padding was placed within the head coil to limit movement during the scan. Resting-state scans were acquired after 3DT1 scans and before DTI scans, no task-based experiments were completed.

_EnumKey_: thyrotoxicosis without mention of goiter or other cause and without mention of thyrotoxic crisis or storm
